amplitude is comparable to the beach length. One is the Maclaurin
expansion of the solution around the moving shoreline, and the other
is Riemann's representation of the solution, which exactly satisfies
the one-dimensional NLSWE and the boundary conditions. After doing a
consistency check by confirming that Riemann's method, a numerical
solution, agrees with the exact solution for an infinitely long,
sloping beach, we assumed that the Maclaurin series solution can also
describe wave motion in the swash zone properly not only for this
model but also for our 'wavy', finite beach model.
