of evolutions with linear operators so that the eigenvalues of the linear operator
are integrals of the nonlinear equation. A striking instance of such a procedure is
the discovery by Gardner, Miura and Kruskal that the eigenvalues of the Schr-dinger operator are integrals of the Korteweg-de Vries equation.
