concerning the existence of double wave solutions of the Korteweg-de Vries
equation, i.e., of solutions which for $|t|$ large behave as the superposition of two
solitary waves travelling at different speeds. The main tool used is the first of a
remarkable series of integrals discovered by Kruskal and Zabusky.
},
